"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The seaborn heatmap function expects a 2D array-like structure (such as a 2D numpy array or a DataFrame with numeric values) as input. The 'tips' DataFrame contains non-numeric columns (like 'sex', 'smoker', 'day', and 'time'), which will cause an error when passed directly to sns.heatmap.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< g = sns.heatmap(tips, square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\\n---\\n> g = sns.heatmap(tips.pivot_table(index='day', columns='sex', values='tip', aggfunc='mean'), square=True, cbar_kws={'fraction': 0.01}, cmap='OrRd', linewidth=1)\"\n}"